race.comment: HOLDING COMPANY (14) finished second, beaten 1.3 lengths, over 1646m at Tampa Bay Downs (Dirt) on debut eight months ago and has been kept under wraps since. Tricky draw to overcome but expected to play a major role. MY SHERRONA (2) turned in a nice effort last time out at the second run of the campaign and finished just 0.3 lengths from the winner in second over 1609m at Saratoga after being in contention on the bend. Perfectly placed and is sure to give this a mighty shake. CLEOPATRA'S KEY (13) turned in a sound effort last time but found a couple better at Saratoga (Turf) over 1609m, beaten 1.5 lengths. That run should have her rock-hard fit now. Junior Alvarado stays aboard and although yet to win has been in the money on two occasions. Capable of running a bold race. JUST JULES (7) returned from a spell a month ago when she was beaten 3.5 lengths into fifth over 1408m at Kentucky. Strips fitter and can figure in the finish. Something for the Multiples: KEY ACTRESS (9)
